
	HARARE - President Emmerson Mnangagwa has appointed Patrick Chinamasa Acting Minister of Finance and Economic Development and Simbarashe Mumbengegwi Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs until a new Cabinet is formed. 
	According to a statement made by the Chief Secretary to the President and Cabinet Dr Misheck Sibanda, these appointments are to allow uninterrupted services in these two critical government ministries. 
	 
	Patrick Chinamasa - Acting Minister of Finance and Economic Development 
	Cabinet was dissolved by President Emmerson Mnangagwa following his recent elevation as President of Zimbabwe. 
	 
	Simbarashe Mumbengegwi - Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs 
	




